15. Use Floating Action Button Widget in Flutter App Development


✅ Explanation (Exam-Oriented)

The FloatingActionButton (FAB) in Flutter is a circular button that floats above the UI, usually at the bottom-right corner of the screen.

It is used for:

Primary or most important action (e.g., add, create, edit)
Quick access to a feature

//main code

import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(MyApp());
}

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      home: FloatingButtonExample(),
    );
  }
}

class FloatingButtonExample extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(
        title: Text("Floating Action Button Example"),
      ),
      body: Center(
        child: Text("Press the button"),
      ),
      floatingActionButton: FloatingActionButton(
        onPressed: () {
          print("FAB Clicked");
        },
        backgroundColor: Colors.blue,
        child: Icon(Icons.add),
      ),
    );
  }
}
